# React Patterns (App Only)

**App-only**: This rule applies only when working in the ClaimStation app (`claimstation-app`). Ignore it when working in claimstation-www or other directories.

## Component Structure

Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces for props.

```tsx
interface ClaimCardProps {
  claim: Claim;
  onStatusChange?: (status: ClaimStatus) => void;
}

export function ClaimCard({ claim, onStatusChange }: ClaimCardProps) {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>{claim.description}</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

## Server vs Client Components

- Default to Server Components
- Add `'use client'` only when needed (hooks, browser APIs, interactivity)
- Keep client components small and leaf-level

## Data Fetching

Use React Query for client-side data fetching.

## Forms

Use React Hook Form with Zod validation.

## UI Components

Use shadcn/ui components. Import from `@/components/ui/` (within claimstation-app).
